ANC Secretary-General Ace Magashule will brief the media on the outcomes of the party's NEC meeting, which concluded on Tuesday. Editor's note: This event will be broadcast live on eNCA.com and DStv Now and is expected to start at 3pm. PRETORIA - ANC Secretary-General Ace Magashule will address the media on Thursday afternoon, to brief the country on the rest of the ANC NEC meeting outcomes. The meeting was held virtually from Sunday to Tuesday. The agenda spanned some difficult issues facing the governing party including corruption, gender-based violence, and party unity. SUMMARY: Ramaphosa concludes NEC meeting Magashule is set to face the ANC Integrity Committee on Saturday. READ: Magashule to appear before ANC's Integrity Committee His appearance is in connection with his alleged involvement in corrupt activities during his tenure as Free State Premier. He is facing 21 charges of fraud, corruption, and money laundering.